			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">What are your opinions on the &quot;Melody&quot; feature for bards?<a name="71804"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 4 05 2:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This thread is not meant for flaming, but for people to express honest opinions. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
I've played a bard since just after Luclin came out. On my old account I lvled one to 56, then sold the acct when we moved. Was out for a year and just recently came back. My new bard is now lvl 38 and going strong. 
<br />

<br />
I haven't personally tried using the melody thing. When I first heard about it, my very first impression of the idea was that it was going to create a lot of very lazy bards.
<br />

<br />
People say that the bard class is so hard to play because you have to melee, twist songs, do crowd control, and everything else all at the same time. I say the reason I'm so proud to play the bard class and be GOOD at it, is that I CAN melee, twist songs, do crowd control and everything else at the same time. 
<br />

<br />
My opinion, if you never played a bard before &quot;Melody&quot; because you thought it was too hard of a class, maybe you should consider not using it right away to get a good feel for the class and how it works.
<br />

<br />
Your thoughts?</span></td>
