				<td colspan="2"><span>i don't use it myself with missed notes the way they are I just don't trust it to work as well as it could . I use a clicky as part of my main twist and it doesn't support that as well. I think this is another one of those if you like it use it, if you don't enjoy it don't use it  problems. After all it has its pros and cons just like manually but personaly with my play style I am still manually twisting.
<br />

<br />
Personally to me if you have the twisting aspect down thats just physical strain which for me currently isn't to much of a problem as I am young enough to recover fairly quickly. To me the hard part of being a bard is just adapting to ever changing roles you have and working with tools you have at hands. That and I guess I just like keeping my hands busy while I play and manually twisting give me that option instead of sitting there since we have no skills we can use in battle beyond singing songs. </span></td>
