				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What are your opinions on the &quot;Melody&quot; feature for bards?<a name="71835"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 4 05 1:42 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Throwing in my 2cp:
<br />

<br />
Overall, I like it.  Typically only use it when I'm in the group meleeing, but for those long XP grinds, it's nice to walk away at the end of the day and not have to icepack my hand from twisting.
<br />

<br />
Don't have any anti-fizzle AA's yet, so it's not very reliable... but in normal XP situations, I don't think letting one song drop sometimes is going to be a killer.  Named and such, typically twist manually since it's more reliable.  Never used to twist 4 songs constantly (saved for special occasions when the extra edge was important), since it hurt too much at the end of a long day, do now.
<br />

<br />
Took a bit to figure out which songs needed a blank /melody so the twist didn't resume, and which didn't... still swap mezz back and forth with /stopsong and /melody, depending on whether a resisted mezz will normally be dangerous, or just irritating.
<br />

<br />
I find my positioning on mobs/relative to casters is better now, since I can free up some of the attention I was paying to twisting.
<br />

<br />
Like the auto-restart feature, helps a lot in resuming a twist on fizzle or bash iterrupt, mildly irritating occasionally.
<br />

<br />
Overall:  It's another tool in the toolbox.  I am a bard, flexibility requires tools, and knowing when/how to use them.  More tools = better bard in the long run.
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />
</span></td>
